description.p:
a pump, which has the functions of sucking, pumping, and jetting water and the strength of which can be adjusted by a control circuit;


a pad, which is a pad of monocoque; wherein the top end of said pad is covered with a hollowed cylinder for accommodating said pump and the lower part of said pad is an extended long pad fitting to the human height, within which pad are distributed with many incoming water ways and outgoing water ways, and on top surface and along the rim of which are equipped with many water inlets and outlets connecting to the water ways;


a control circuit, which is placed within the hollowed cylinder and connected to a wired switch via which the user is to control the strength of the pump.

